The author extends their best wishes to Muslim communities as they begin the holy month of Ramadan. They reaffirm their support to Muslim communities suffering hardships and devastation, such as those affected by earthquakes in Turkey and Syria, and floods in Pakistan. The author also emphasizes the importance of the universal human right to practice, pray, and preach faith peacefully and openly. They express solidarity with Muslims facing oppression, including Uyghurs in China and Rohingya in Burma. The author also honors Muslim communities in the United States and their contributions to various fields. They call for unity and a commitment to creating a more equal, just, tolerant, and compassionate nation.